And in fact, if, I think
if you look at the history

00:35:01.040 --> 00:35:02.570
of the world, like

00:35:02.570 --> 00:35:04.280
that's just been
happening for a long time.

00:35:04.280 --> 00:35:05.750
The thing I think the
world is not ready for.

00:35:05.750 --> 00:35:08.000
Like people have maybe
abstractly thought like, okay,

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:09.260
it's gonna be a better programmer than me.

00:35:09.260 --> 00:35:10.430
It's gonna be, you know,

00:35:10.430 --> 00:35:12.650
better at customer support and whatever.

00:35:12.650 --> 00:35:14.210
I don't think the world
has really had the humanoid

00:35:14.210 --> 00:35:16.160
robots moment yet.

00:35:16.160 --> 00:35:19.100
Like the first day you're
like walking down the street

00:35:19.100 --> 00:35:20.270
and there's like seven robots

00:35:20.270 --> 00:35:21.950
that walk past you doing
things or whatever.

00:35:21.950 --> 00:35:23.390
It's gonna feel very sci-fi.

00:35:24.230 --> 00:35:26.480
And I don't think that's very
far away from like a visceral

00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:27.920
like, oh man, this is gonna do a lot

00:35:27.920 --> 00:35:28.970
of things that people used to do.

00:35:28.970 --> 00:35:30.740
So, so yeah, it's coming

00:35:30.740 --> 00:35:33.380
and we, we have always tried
to just be super honest about

00:35:33.380 --> 00:35:35.150
what we think the impact may be.

00:35:35.150 --> 00:35:37.250
Realizing that we'll be
wrong on a lot of details.

00:35:39.540 --> 00:35:40.950
Lately, predicting the future

00:35:40.950 --> 00:35:43.050
of AI seems harder than usual.

00:35:45.120 --> 00:35:48.960
In a few moments I will sign
a historic executive order,

00:35:48.960 --> 00:35:51.870
instituting reciprocal tariffs.

00:35:52.710 --> 00:35:53.910
President Trump's tariffs

00:35:53.910 --> 00:35:55.230
and the increasing volatility

00:35:55.230 --> 00:35:58.080
of geopolitics have created
potential challenges

00:35:58.080 --> 00:36:00.180
for the AI infrastructure boom

00:36:00.180 --> 00:36:02.460
and shaken up the race to dominate AI

00:36:02.460 --> 00:36:03.293
between the US and China.

00:36:03.293 --> 00:36:04.126
Technology faces rising costs.

00:36:05.153 --> 00:36:05.986
Building these data centers

00:36:05.986 --> 00:36:06.819
just got conceivably more expensive.

00:36:10.050 --> 00:36:12.900
It's very difficult
to immediately decouple.

00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:19.890
Uncertainty is bad for business.
Instead of moving forward,

00:36:19.890 --> 00:36:22.170
people have war rooms about, oh,

00:36:22.170 --> 00:36:24.210
what's tomorrow gonna look like?

00:36:24.210 --> 00:36:25.890
Former diplomat, Anja Manuel

00:36:25.890 --> 00:36:28.560
and Bloomberg, Shirin Ghaffary
have been closely watching

00:36:28.560 --> 00:36:30.630
how this could impact
projects like Stargate.

00:36:31.665 --> 00:36:33.810
How much does the AI and
data center supply chain

00:36:33.810 --> 00:36:35.670
depend on China?

00:36:35.670 --> 00:36:37.620
Yeah, so a lot of the
materials that are used

00:36:37.620 --> 00:36:39.750
to build data centers, a lot

00:36:39.750 --> 00:36:41.970
of those materials actually
come from China, right?

00:36:41.970 --> 00:36:44.670
Aluminum, steel. China's
a major manufacturer.

00:36:44.670 --> 00:36:46.980
That could be an area of impact on raising

00:36:46.980 --> 00:36:48.540
construction center costs.

00:36:49.470 --> 00:36:52.980
Now on the chip side, that's
a much bigger higher cost

00:36:52.980 --> 00:36:54.690
for these companies, right?

00:36:54.690 --> 00:36:57.150
And that there's a lot more uncertainty.

00:36:57.150 --> 00:37:01.260
The most sophisticated chips
are manufactured in Taiwan,

00:37:01.260 --> 00:37:04.530
Korea, Japan often brought to China

00:37:04.530 --> 00:37:06.570
to be integrated into
all of the electronics

00:37:06.570 --> 00:37:07.980
that are in all of our pockets.

00:37:07.980 --> 00:37:09.930
This is a really complex,

00:37:09.930 --> 00:37:11.850
totally international supply chain.

00:37:11.850 --> 00:37:12.900
And I think the takeaway

00:37:12.900 --> 00:37:15.510
for everyone is you cannot just break the

00:37:15.510 --> 00:37:17.010
international trading system.

00:37:17.010 --> 00:37:20.790
And we cannot be a country
that lives in autarky.

00:37:20.790 --> 00:37:22.590
We're always gonna depend on others.

00:37:22.590 --> 00:37:26.310
What does Stargate mean
for the US China tech race?

00:37:26.310 --> 00:37:30.240
I think it's one critical
step in so many steps.

00:37:30.240 --> 00:37:32.160
When you look at the race that's on

00:37:32.160 --> 00:37:34.110
between the US and China.

00:37:34.110 --> 00:37:36.240
We're in a real race. The Chinese are

00:37:36.240 --> 00:37:37.650
giving us a run for their money.

00:37:37.650 --> 00:37:38.880
China's right behind us.

00:37:38.880 --> 00:37:40.710
I mean they're, we're very, very close.

00:37:40.710 --> 00:37:43.950
50% of the world's AI
researchers are Chinese.

00:37:43.950 --> 00:37:46.380
That doesn't mean we can't
collaborate with the Chinese

00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:49.560
and certainly means we
should keep talking to them.

00:37:49.560 --> 00:37:52.590
But where you used to
have some level of trust

00:37:52.590 --> 00:37:55.320
and some level of communication,
now you don't have it.

00:37:55.320 --> 00:37:57.600
And I worry that the tariffs not directly,

00:37:57.600 --> 00:38:01.770
but indirectly are making
us lose that kind of trust.

00:38:01.770 --> 00:38:03.000
Now that we're in this position,

00:38:03.000 --> 00:38:05.310
there's obviously this tension
between the US and China.

00:38:05.310 --> 00:38:09.030
Is this an opportunity
to do it a different way

00:38:09.030 --> 00:38:10.950
to build data centers a different way?

00:38:10.950 --> 00:38:12.120
I think that's exactly right.

00:38:12.120 --> 00:38:14.190
This is an opportunity
to do it differently.

00:38:14.190 --> 00:38:17.670
What I would like to see is that

00:38:17.670 --> 00:38:19.950
more advanced manufacturing

00:38:19.950 --> 00:38:22.890
of the most sophisticated
chips happens here.

00:38:22.890 --> 00:38:24.990
And I think TSMC is doing some of that.

00:38:24.990 --> 00:38:27.480
Others, the CHIPS Act really helped.

00:38:27.480 --> 00:38:30.750
Also, going back to
Stargate, those data centers

00:38:30.750 --> 00:38:32.190
and all of the AI training

00:38:32.190 --> 00:38:33.750
and the AI inference shouldn't just be

00:38:33.750 --> 00:38:34.920
happening in the United States.

00:38:34.920 --> 00:38:37.630
It be happening in friendly
allied countries as well.

00:38:37.630 --> 00:38:39.760
Iceland, Greenland, the
Nordics that have lots

00:38:39.760 --> 00:38:41.680
of geothermal power
should be a part of it.

00:38:41.680 --> 00:38:43.060
Europe should be a part of it.

00:38:43.060 --> 00:38:45.910
Japan, our friends in Asia, Singapore,

00:38:45.910 --> 00:38:48.970
there's really an opportunity
here to have a community

00:38:48.970 --> 00:38:52.510
of like-minded countries
that are doing this together.

00:38:52.510 --> 00:38:55.420
Is President Trump alienating many

00:38:55.420 --> 00:38:56.440
countries that would be our

00:38:56.440 --> 00:38:58.300
allies in this endeavor?

00:38:58.300 --> 00:38:59.470
Yes. Some of our friends

00:38:59.470 --> 00:39:02.110
and allies feel a little bit alienated.

00:39:02.110 --> 00:39:04.480
I hope ultimately that won't be the case.

00:39:04.480 --> 00:39:08.350
I think increasingly the
administration will understand

00:39:08.350 --> 00:39:12.010
how important our partners are
and how much they add to us.

00:39:12.010 --> 00:39:15.820
And so I actually believe
will come out okay in the end.

00:39:19.900 --> 00:39:21.340
There are still many questions about

00:39:21.340 --> 00:39:22.990
where the business of AI is headed.

00:39:23.830 --> 00:39:24.850
The expense of building

00:39:24.850 --> 00:39:26.500
and running these data centers makes it

00:39:26.500 --> 00:39:28.390
tough to turn a profit.

00:39:28.390 --> 00:39:32.440
OpenAI, for example, ran
a $5 billion loss in 2024.

00:39:33.730 --> 00:39:36.070
And there's no guarantee that
simply adding huge amounts

00:39:36.070 --> 00:39:38.110
of compute will make AI models smart

00:39:38.110 --> 00:39:40.480
and reliable enough to
be truly transformative.

00:39:42.070 --> 00:39:45.460
So as solid and substantial
as Stargate might seem,

00:39:45.460 --> 00:39:50.460
it's surrounded by uncertainty
about how smart AI can get,

00:39:50.680 --> 00:39:52.300
which bets will pay off

00:39:52.300 --> 00:39:54.370
and what kind of future we're creating.

00:39:56.290 --> 00:39:58.870
The tech industry goes
through booms and busts.

00:39:58.870 --> 00:40:01.360
AI goes through winters and springs.

00:40:01.360 --> 00:40:02.193
How long is this boom gonna last...

00:40:03.026 --> 00:40:06.160
I think this boom has
quite a bit of legs to it.

00:40:06.160 --> 00:40:08.560
You just sort of look at
the long-term investments

00:40:08.560 --> 00:40:10.200
that the biggest companies
in the world are,

00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:11.380
are making in this.

00:40:11.380 --> 00:40:13.300
And I think, you know, even

00:40:13.300 --> 00:40:16.240
with things coming out
like DeepSeek you know,

00:40:16.240 --> 00:40:18.490
I think everybody's
pretty unanimous in terms

00:40:18.490 --> 00:40:20.140
of we're staying the course.

00:40:20.140 --> 00:40:24.400
What's required for AI to scale
is a lot more infrastructure

00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:25.330
and there's a bigger risk to

00:40:25.330 --> 00:40:27.010
underinvestment than over investment.

00:40:29.650 --> 00:40:32.620
If ChatGPT were to
discover a Stargate,

00:40:32.620 --> 00:40:35.380
a futuristic wormhole
that we could

00:40:35.380 --> 00:40:36.213
all travel through

00:40:36.213 --> 00:40:37.046
what's on

00:40:37.046 --> 00:40:37.879
the other side?

00:40:37.879 --> 00:40:41.080
If ChatGPT could like
transport us to the future?

00:40:41.080 --> 00:40:41.913
Yeah.

00:40:41.913 --> 00:40:42.746
I mean, no, no, no one knows, right?

00:40:43.900 --> 00:40:48.160
Do I think I could have sat here in 1905

00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:51.100
and told you what we were
about to discover in physics

00:40:52.090 --> 00:40:54.700
and that 40 years later we
would like have an atomic bomb?

00:40:55.570 --> 00:40:57.670
Definitely not.

00:40:57.670 --> 00:41:01.870
And I, I think I am way too
self-aware of my own limitations

00:41:01.870 --> 00:41:03.820
to sit here and try to
say I can like tell you

00:41:03.820 --> 00:41:06.460
what's on the other side of
that wormhole. I have no idea.

00:41:06.460 --> 00:41:08.230
But net. Net good. Yes.

00:41:08.230 --> 00:41:09.940
Up and down. Not better in every way,

00:41:09.940 --> 00:41:12.790
but yeah, I think up to the
right, yeah, up into the right

00:41:12.790 --> 00:41:13.690
with some choppiness.

